The paper proposes a model for open-domain question answering, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. The model involves a retriever-reader architecture, which suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in deep learning models for NLP, suggesting that it could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE).
